@startuml role_hierarchy
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA

card GUEST #FFE0E0 [
  <b>GUEST (Unauthenticated)
  ---
  OK Browse wines, winemakers, shops
  OK Browse approved events
  OK Add to cart
  OK View reviews

  NO Checkout
  NO Create content
  NO Register for events
]

card CUSTOMER #E0F2F1 [
  <b>CUSTOMER (Registered)
  ---
  OK All GUEST permissions
  OK Checkout & create orders
  OK Manage addresses
  OK Register for events
  OK Write reviews/comments
  OK Request Winemaker role
  OK Request Shop Owner role

  NO Create wine/events
]

card WINEMAKER #FFF9C4 [
  <b>WINEMAKER (Role acquired)
  ---
  OK All CUSTOMER permissions
  OK Create/edit/delete wines
  OK Create/edit/manage events
  OK View event dashboard
  OK Can be SHOP_OWNER simultaneously

  NO Approve own events
  NO Manage shops
]

card SHOPOWNER #F3E5F5 [
  <b>SHOP OWNER (Role acquired)
  ---
  OK All CUSTOMER permissions
  OK Create/edit/delete shop
  OK Manage products & inventory
  OK Create wine bundles
  OK Set availability & hours
  OK View/update incoming orders
  OK Can be WINEMAKER simultaneously
]

card ADMIN #FFCCBC [
  <b>ADMIN (Staff member)
  ---
  OK Full access to all features
  OK Approve/reject role requests
  OK Approve/reject events
  OK Manage all users
  OK Moderate reviews/comments
  OK View platform statistics
  OK Back-office access
]

GUEST --|> CUSTOMER : registers
CUSTOMER --|> WINEMAKER : approved
CUSTOMER --|> SHOPOWNER : approved
CUSTOMER --|> ADMIN : staff assignment

note right of ADMIN
  <b>Key Rules:
  - One user can have multiple roles
  - Roles acquired via approval
  - ADMIN is separate (staff only)
  - See roles.md for matrix
end note

@enduml
